metadata.name: Wall of Chart #107
A Bugged Forest #355
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Terrain Series, Quilt #24
metadata.description:
The first release from my experiments with terrain generation. 

Method: A quadtree is created from N number of randomly generated points. For each rectangle in the tree, particle points are created based on poisson disc sampling. The movement of these particles along the terrain + noise field is drawn with my rake-stroke method. The color of the rake-stroke is based on the noise value at the origin along with some other variability.

The loading time of the piece will be longer for some variations.

metadata.name: Patches #218
metadata.description:
This token generates a colorful abstract artwork that appears as watercolor on fabric. Project began as exploration of palettes used in famous masterpieces listed on Color Lisa web site. 97 color combinations used by great artists are applied here on abstract art.

Each piece is generated by bio inspired cellular automata in which colors from chosen palette are competing for domination on canvas. There are three different configurations of space fragmentation and each one is producing specific style.

metadata.name: primordial soup #181
metadata.description:
1024 kinematic automata that imitate living organisms, leaving behind a trace of paint before going extinct. Blotches of paint are deposited by these nodes that attract and repulse each other according to rules based on their color and size.

Short description of features:
- mood: the palette
- tone: the noisiness
- flow: the number of neighbors affecting each node
- brow: the brush size
- delirium: brush modifier
- distancing: kinetic rule modifier

Each feature is equally likely - rarity is in the eye of the beholder.

@balidani
